<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idefb01bf8-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db" identifier="/us/usc/t54/s320104"><num value="320104">§ 320104.</num><heading> Jurisdiction of States in acquired land</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be held to deprive any State, or political subdivision of a State, of its civil and criminal jurisdiction in and over land acquired by the United States under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idefb01bf9-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db">(<ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s3">Pub. L. 113–287, § 3</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3259">128 Stat. 3259</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
